text: Imliwati Lemtur (born 25 December 1991) is an Indian cricketer. He made his List A debut for Nagaland in the 2018–19 Vijay Hazare Trophy on 19 September 2018. He was the leading wicket-taker for Nagaland in the 2018–19 Vijay Hazare Trophy, with ten dismissals in seven matches. He made his first-class debut for Nagaland in the 2018–19 Ranji Trophy on 1 November 2018. He made his Twenty20 debut for Nagaland in the 2018–19 Syed Mushtaq Ali Trophy on 21 February 2019. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1991 births Category:Living people Category:Indian cricketers Category:Nagaland cricketers Category:Place of birth missing (living people)
